Subdomain Setup Documentation (Cloudflare)

Overview

This document explains how to create the subdomain edinai.yourdomain.com and point it to the server IP
13.234.223.188 using Cloudflare DNS.

Step 1: Open Cloudflare Dashboard

1. Go to https://dash.cloudflare.com

2. Select your domain (example: yourdomain.com)

3. Open the DNS - Records page.

Step 2: Add New DNS Record

Add a new DNS record with the following values:

Type: A

Name: EDINAI

IPv4 Address: 13.234,223.188

Proxy Status: DNS Only (Grey cloud)

TTL: Auto

Step 3: Subdomain Created
Y our new subdomain is: edinai.yourdomain.com

It now points to: 13.234.223.188

Notes
- DNS propagation may take 1-10 minutes.
- The server must run on port 80 or 443.

- For HTTPS (SSL), use Certbot or Cloudflare SSL.

Hostinger Note
 No need to create a subdomain in Hostinger because this subdomain points to an AWS ६९२2 server, not Hostinger
hosting.

Setup Complete.
